This class provides the primary API for measuring distance (range) to other devices using the * IEEE 802.11mc Wi-Fi Round Trip Time (RTT) technology.

Wi-Fi RTT may not be usable at some points, e.g. when Wi-Fi is disabled. To validate that * the functionality is available use the {@link #isAvailable()} function. To track * changes in RTT usability register for the {@link #ACTION_WIFI_RTT_STATE_CHANGED} * broadcast. Note that this broadcast is not sticky - you should register for it and then * check the above API to avoid a race condition.
